<!-- ========== SECTION 01: CODE EDITORS & IDEs ========== -->
<section class="res-section" id="code-editors" aria-label="Code Editors and IDEs">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="section-header">
      <span class="section-number">[01]</span>
      <h2>Code Editors & IDEs</h2>
    </div>
    <p class="section-desc">Your code editor is where you'll spend most of your development time. The difference between a good editor and a great one isn't just features  |  it's how well those features integrate into your workflow, how quickly you can navigate large codebases, and how effectively it helps you catch mistakes before they become bugs.</p>

    <!-- VS Code -->
    <article class="tool-review" id="vscode" aria-label="Visual Studio Code Review">
      <div class="tool-review-header">
        <div class="tool-review-title-row">
          <h3 class="tool-review-name">Visual Studio Code (VS Code)</h3>
          <div class="tool-review-tags">
            <span class="tag tag-free">Free</span>
            <span class="tag">Cross-platform</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="tool-review-body">
        <div class="tool-review-about">
          <p><strong>What it is:</strong> Microsoft's open-source, lightweight code editor that has become the de facto standard for web development and increasingly for other languages. It's technically an editor, not a full IDE, but with extensions it can match or exceed IDE functionality.</p>
          <p><strong>Why it matters:</strong> VS Code strikes the perfect balance between simplicity and power. It starts fast, stays responsive with large projects, and has an extension marketplace that covers virtually every language, framework, and workflow imaginable.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="tool-review-features">
          <h3>Key Features</h3>
          <ul class="feature-list">
            <li><strong>IntelliSense:</strong> Context-aware code completion that understands your project's types and APIs</li>
            <li><strong>Integrated debugging:</strong> Set breakpoints, step through code, inspect variables  |  all without leaving the editor</li>
            <li><strong>Built-in Git integration:</strong> Commit, push, pull, resolve merge conflicts visually</li>
            <li><strong>Extensions ecosystem:</strong> Over 30,000 extensions covering languages, themes, debuggers, and tools</li>
            <li><strong>Live Share:</strong> Real-time collaborative editing and debugging with teammates</li>
            <li><strong>Remote development:</strong> Edit code on remote servers, WSL, or containers as if it were local</li>
            <li><strong>Terminal integration:</strong> Multiple terminals, split views, tasks automation</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="tool-review-usecases">
          <h3>Best Use Cases</h3>
          <ul class="usecase-list">
            <li>Web development (JavaScript, TypeScript, React, Vue, Angular)</li>
            <li>Python development with strong extension support</li>
            <li>Multi-language projects where you switch contexts frequently</li>
            <li>Teams that need consistent, shareable development environments</li>
            <li>Remote work and cloud development scenarios</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="tool-review-grid">
          <div class="tool-review-pros">
            <h3>Pros</h3>
            <ul class="pros-list">
              <li>Completely free and open source</li>
              <li>Fast startup and excellent performance</li>
              <li>Massive extension ecosystem</li>
              <li>Great out-of-box experience for web development</li>
              <li>Active development and monthly updates</li>
              <li>Excellent documentation and community</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <div class="tool-review-cons">
            <h3>Cons</h3>
            <ul class="cons-list">
              <li>Can become slow with too many extensions</li>
              <li>Extension quality varies significantly</li>
              <li>Less polished than paid IDEs for certain languages (Java, C#)</li>
              <li>Some advanced refactoring features require extensions</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="tool-review-meta">
          <div class="tool-meta-item">
            <span class="tool-meta-label">Learning Curve</span>
            <div class="learning-curve-bar" aria-label="Learning curve: Easy to start, grows with you">
              <div class="learning-curve-fill learning-curve-easy"></div>
            </div>
            <span class="tool-meta-value">Easy to start, grows with you</span>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="tool-review-cta">
          <a href="<https://code.visualstudio.com>" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="btn btn-primary btn-sm">Download VS Code
            <svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M18 13v6a2 2 0 0 1-2 2H5a2 2 0 0 1-2-2V8a2 2 0 0 1 2-2h6"/><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"/><line x1="10" y1="14" x2="21" y2="3"/></svg>
          </a>
        </div>

        <div class="tool-review-tip">
          <svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10"/><path d="M12 16v-4"/><path d="M12 8h.01"/></svg>
          <p><strong>Pro tip:</strong> Start with these essential extensions: ESLint/Pylint for linting, Prettier for formatting, GitLens for enhanced Git features, and the language-specific extension pack for your primary language. Install only what you need  |  you can always add more later.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </article>

    <!-- IntelliJ IDEA -->
    <article class="tool-review" id="intellij" aria-label="IntelliJ IDEA Review">
      <div class="tool-review-header">
        <div class="tool-review-title-row">
          <h3 class="tool-review-name">JetBrains IntelliJ IDEA</h3>
          <div class="tool-review-tags">
            <span class="tag tag-freemium">Free + Paid</span>
            <span class="tag">Cross-platform</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="tool-review-body">
        <div class="tool-review-about">
          <p><strong>What it is:</strong> A full-featured IDE primarily designed for Java development, but the Ultimate edition supports virtually every major language and framework. Known for intelligent code assistance and powerful refactoring tools.</p>
          <p><strong>Why it matters:</strong> IntelliJ represents the gold standard for IDE intelligence. Its code analysis, refactoring capabilities, and framework integration are unmatched, particularly for JVM languages and enterprise development.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="tool-review-features">
          <h3>Key Features</h3>
          <ul class="feature-list">
            <li><strong>Smart code completion:</strong> Deep understanding of your codebase enables highly accurate suggestions</li>
            <li><strong>Advanced refactoring:</strong> Rename, extract, inline, and restructure code safely across entire projects</li>
            <li><strong>Framework support:</strong> First-class integration for Spring, Jakarta EE, Micronaut, and more</li>
            <li><strong>Database tools:</strong> Built-in database client with query console and schema management</li>
            <li><strong>Version control:</strong> Superior Git integration with visual merge tools and local history</li>
            <li><strong>Debugger:</strong> Powerful debugging with expression evaluation and memory view</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="tool-review-usecases">
          <h3>Best Use Cases</h3>
          <ul class="usecase-list">
            <li>Java and Kotlin development (Android, backend, enterprise)</li>
            <li>Large enterprise codebases requiring sophisticated refactoring</li>
            <li>Projects using Spring, Jakarta EE, or other complex frameworks</li>
            <li>Full-stack development with Ultimate edition (Java + JavaScript frameworks)</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="tool-review-grid">
          <div class="tool-review-pros">
            <h3>Pros</h3>
            <ul class="pros-list">
              <li>Best-in-class Java support and refactoring</li>
              <li>Community edition is free for Java/Kotlin/Scala</li>
              <li>Excellent code analysis catches bugs early</li>
              <li>Deeply integrated frameworks and tools</li>
              <li>Built-in tools reduce need for separate apps</li>
