<!-- ========== SECTION 02: VERSION CONTROL ========== -->
<section class="res-section res-section-alt" id="version-control" aria-label="Version Control Tools">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="section-header">
      <span class="section-number">[02]</span>
      <h2>Version Control Tools</h2>
    </div>
    <p class="section-desc">Version control is non-negotiable in modern development. It's your safety net, your collaboration tool, and your project history all in one. Understanding version control well will save you from disasters and make you a better team member.</p>

    <!-- Git -->
    <article class="tool-review" id="git" aria-label="Git Review">
      <div class="tool-review-header">
        <div class="tool-review-title-row">
          <h3 class="tool-review-name">Git</h3>
          <div class="tool-review-tags">
            <span class="tag tag-free">Free</span>
            <span class="tag">Cross-platform</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="tool-review-body">
        <div class="tool-review-about">
          <p><strong>What it is:</strong> The distributed version control system that has become the industry standard. Created by Linus Torvalds for Linux kernel development, now used by virtually every software project.</p>
          <p><strong>Why it matters:</strong> Git is the foundation of modern collaborative development. Whether you work alone or on a team of thousands, Git tracks every change, enables parallel work through branching, and makes it safe to experiment.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="tool-review-features">
          <h3>Core Capabilities</h3>
          <ul class="feature-list">
            <li><strong>Commits:</strong> Snapshots of your project at specific points in time</li>
            <li><strong>Branches:</strong> Isolated development lines for features, fixes, or experiments</li>
            <li><strong>Merging:</strong> Combining changes from different branches</li>
            <li><strong>Rebasing:</strong> Rewriting history for cleaner project timelines</li>
            <li><strong>Distributed:</strong> Every developer has the full project history</li>
            <li><strong>Staging area:</strong> Review and organize changes before committing</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="tool-review-commands">
          <h3>Essential Commands to Master</h3>
          <div class="commands-grid">
            <div class="command-item">
              <code>git status</code>
              <span>See what's changed and what's staged</span>
            </div>
            <div class="command-item">
              <code>git diff</code>
              <span>Review changes before committing</span>
            </div>
            <div class="command-item">
              <code>git log</code>
              <span>Explore project history</span>
            </div>
            <div class="command-item">
